# Full URLs for site pages

When showing the user URLs for **this product's website** (marketing pages, app routes, API paths meant to be opened in a browser), use **full absolute URLs** — never bare paths like `/where-to-stay-in-paris` or `where-to-stay-in-paris`.

## Canonical origin

Default to **`https://www.travelbyvibe.com`** unless the context clearly requires another host (e.g. `https://roommatch-1fg5.onrender.com` for Render debugging).

## Examples

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `/where-to-stay-in-paris` | `https://www.travelbyvibe.com/where-to-stay-in-paris` |
| `paris-hotels` | `https://www.travelbyvibe.com/paris-hotels` |
| `?city=Mexico City` | `https://www.travelbyvibe.com/?city=Mexico%20City` |

## When this applies

- Spot-check lists after deploy
- SEO / indexing discussions
- “Open this page” suggestions
- Comparing live vs local (still show full URL for the live site)

## Exceptions

- **Code and config** may keep path-only form (`/api/vsearch`, Express routes, sitemap entries) when editing files.
- **Third-party URLs** (GitHub, Supabase, LiteAPI, etc.) — use their full URLs as usual; this rule is for TravelByVibe site links shown to the user.
